          <h1 class="infoh1">Information</h1>
          <p class="infop">
            Biodiversity loss, also called loss of biodiversity, is a decrease
            in biodiversity within a species, an ecosystem, a given geographic
            area, or Earth as a whole. Biodiversity, or biological diversity, is
            a term that refers to the number of genes, species, and individual
            organisms within a given species, and biological communities within
            a defined geographic area, ranging from the smallest ecosystem to
            the global biosphere.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
